						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">MetalSlime wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Another thing you might add to the templates would be bank-switching code, PRG and CHR where applicable.  If the mappers are configurable you could set up environment variables and conditional assembly.  It would make the templates easier to use right out of the box.</div>
<br />That's what I'm trying to do with my "framework" for neshla. It has a file for mapper capabilities, such as mirroring, chr banking, prg banking... And uses #ifdef areas depending on mapper defined for de project.
<br />Currently supports: 
<br />MMC1, MMC3, AXROM, GXROM, CPROM, BXROM, UXROM, CNROM
<br />
<br />Header file-&gt; <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://neshlagamefw.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/neshlagamefw/bin/include/nesex/nes_mappers_ex.h?revision=1&amp;content-type=text%2Fplain">http://neshlagamefw.svn.sourceforge.net ... xt%2Fplain</a><!-- m -->
<br />ASM file -&gt; <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://neshlagamefw.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/neshlagamefw/bin/lib/nesex/nes_mappers_ex.as?revision=1&amp;content-type=text%2Fplain">http://neshlagamefw.svn.sourceforge.net ... xt%2Fplain</a><!-- m --></div>

